  "text": "Changes in inflammatory markers after 26 weeks of tesamorelin administration Treatment with tesamorelin was associated with a small but significant decrease in tPA antigen (À2.2 AE 2.5 vs. À1.6 AE 2.9 ng/ml, tesamorelin vs. placebo, P ¼ 0.03) as compared to placebo (Table 3 ). Change in PAI-1 antigen in the tesamorelin group was not significantly different from placebo (À2.5 AE 16.9 vs. À1.0 AE 17.3 ng/ml, tesamorelin vs. placebo, P ¼ 0.34, Table 3 ). As previously reported, adiponectin modestly but significantly increased from baseline in tesamorelin-treated patients (0.5 AE 2.7 vs. À0.1 AE 1.3 mg/ml, tesamorelin vs. placebo, respectively, P ¼ 0.03), and CRP did not significantly change with tesamorelin treatment (Table 3 ) [CITATION_1] .",
